headline: NetApp Q1 Outlook Falls Short, Analyst Lowers Price Forecast
summary: NetApp, Inc. (NASDAQ:NTAP) reported fiscal fourth-quarter results on Thursday. The company reported quarterly sales of $1.73 billion (+4% year over year), beating the Street view of $1.72 billion. The company reported adjusted earnings per share of $1.93, beating the analyst consensus estimate of $1.90. Following the results, Wells Fargo analyst Aaron Rakers maintains NetApp with an Equal Weight rating, lowering the price forecast from $115 to $100. Also Read: Trump’s $6 Trillion Investment Deal
